1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the capacity region of a wireless relay channel, which is a classic problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies a wireless two-way relay channel, which is a fundamental problem in wireless networking. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents an optimal beamforming structure and an efficient algorithm to compute the optimal beamforming matrix, which are related to control and optimization. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the achievable rates of different beamforming schemes, which are related to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the design and optimization of wireless communication systems, which can have social and economic impacts.
